<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/bethany-shinkins> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Professor Bethany Shinkins is a Professor of Health Economics at Warwick Medical School at the University of Warwick. Bethany has a longstanding interest in screening and is a test expert member of the UK National Screening Committee. She is a co-investigator on the Yorkshire Lung Screening Trial, a randomised controlled trial to evaluate community-based low-dose CT screening for lung cancer, and iDx-LUNG which is a biomarker study embedded within the Lung Health Check."@en .
